				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Another way to get nearly uniformly distributed numbers from 0 to 4 without the time-uncertainty of looping calls to your RNG is to multiply the RNG's output by 5.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">jsr random<br /><br />; Multiply A by 5/4 and keep bits 8-6<br />sta tmp0<br />lsr a<br />lsr a<br />clc<br />adc tmp0&nbsp; ; C:A = 0 to 319<br />and #$C0&nbsp; ; C:A = 0, 64, 128, 192, or 256<br />rol a<br />rol a<br />rol a<br /></div><br /><br />For 5 choices in particular, you can treat values 0-203 one way and 204-255 another, such as returning 4 for all values 204+ and using bits 1-0 of values 0-203.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">jsr random<br />cmp #204<br />bcc not4<br />&nbsp; lda #4<br />&nbsp; bcs haveA<br />not4:<br />&nbsp; and #$03<br />haveA:<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
